Question: Explain how to reach your home without using any street names
Answer:
To reach my home from Williamsburg, it is quite a journey. You would pick any road nearby with lots of cars on it and go south until you came to a sign that said North Carolina. They you turn west and go for about 400 miles until you reach the mountains. Just before Mt. Rodgers, there is a sign for Oak Hill, where I live in the brick house on the hill.